'''Angus Taylor''' is a Canadian [[Philosophy|philosopher]] specializing in [[animal rights]]. He lectures in philosophy at the [[University of Victoria]] in [[British Columbia]], and is the author of ''Animals and Ethics'' (2003). Taylor argues that to be consistent we must either exclude some humans from the moral community, or include at least some animals.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Angus Taylor |title=Hunting For Consistency |work=Philosophy Now |volume=Issue 67 |date=May–June 2008 |url=http://www.philosophynow.org/contents?issue=67 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531151721/http://www.philosophynow.org/contents?issue=67 |archivedate=May 31, 2009 }}</ref>

