'''Shiba Sonome''' (1664–1726, 斯波 園女) was a [[Japan]]ese [[zen]] [[poet]]. She was an acquaintance and friend of [[Matsuo Bashō]], and their correspondence is a treasure of zen and [[haiku]] history.

Sonome was known for her poetry, which possessed a frank and immediate sense of purpose.

