<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Yukthirekha1.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Cover of ''[[Yukthirekha]]'' magazine (August 2006)]] -->
'''''Yukthirekha''''' is a [[rationalist]] periodical published monthly in [[Malayalam]].<ref name="joh">{{cite book|author=Johannes Quack|title=Disenchanting India: Organized Rationalism and Criticism of Religion in India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=55wFpydSZ8oC&pg=PA168|accessdate=12 February 2016|date=22 November 2011|publisher=Oxford University Press, USA|isbn=978-0-19-981260-8|page=168}}</ref> It was founded in 1984 by [[Kerala Yukthivadi Sangham]], a rationalist and [[Marxist]] group.<ref name="joh"/> [[Pavanan]] was the founder-editor of the magazine. Kesavan Vellikulangara served on the editorial board of the magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Writer Kesavan Vellikulangara dead|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/writer-kesavan-vellikulangara-dead/article5752000.ece|accessdate=12 October 2016|work=The Hindu|date=5 March 2014}}</ref>

